Key Match Events: Nic Claxton scored 10 points on 5 of 8 shooting, grabbed eight rebounds, handed out three assists, notched a couple of steals, and blocked a shot in a season-high 26:38.
Dorian Finney-Smith had 17 points, including a Nets career-high-tying 5 of 8 from deep, with six boards in 28 minutes.
Dorian Finney-Smith became the second player in team history with five 3-pointers and five offensive rebounds in the same game.
Post-Match Reflections: Nic Claxton expressed satisfaction with his performance, emphasizing effort, execution, and grit.
Claxton mentioned his readiness to play and his recovery from a hamstring injury.
Dorian Finney-Smith highlighted the challenges of guarding big men and his determination to win.
Others: Noah Clowney missed the game with a sore hip but is hopeful of playing in the next game against Boston.
Ben Simmons was rested on the tail end of a back-to-back to manage his back.
